public abstract class AqueousSpecie extends Specie
The AqueousSpecie abstract class extends the Specie class and provides a concrete implementation of the SpecieLogic interface by overriding the calculateTransport(double, double) method. It serves as a base class for biogeochemical species with aqueous behavior, providing a default transport calculation based on the specified discharge rate.

    • calculateTransport

      public final double calculateTransport(double amount, double rate)
      Description copied from interface: SpecieLogic
      Calculates the transport of the biogeochemical species based on the given amount and discharge parameters. The transport calculation is influenced by the specific logic associated with the behavior of the species in the freshwater system.
      Parameters:
      amount - The amount of the biogeochemical species.
      rate - The discharge rate in the freshwater system.
      Returns:
      The calculated transport value for the species.
